01:00.413 --> 01:04.375
And so Dr Beckett finds himself
leaping from life to life,

01:04.375 --> 01:07.420
striving to put right
what once went wrong,

01:07.420 --> 01:10.923
and hoping each time
that his next leap

01:10.923 --> 01:12.759
will be the leap home.'

01:12.759 --> 01:14.802
♪ ROCK

01:15.970 --> 01:18.014
(CHEERING)

01:32.111 --> 01:34.447
Are you gonna do it or not?

01:34.447 --> 01:36.032
Come on!

01:38.868 --> 01:39.869
Oh, boy!

02:53.276 --> 02:55.278
♪ ROCK

03:18.509 --> 03:21.220
(CHEERING)

03:26.225 --> 03:29.687
OK, we're coming through.
Move out of our way.

03:29.687 --> 03:33.566
Come on, guys.
Move it! Move it! OK, I got it.

03:35.276 --> 03:38.571
Come on! Get out of our way!
Move it! Come on!

03:48.080 --> 03:49.582
(SCREAMING)

03:49.582 --> 03:51.125
Stop now! Come on!

03:51.125 --> 03:53.753
Let them get in here!
Move on now! Come on!

03:53.753 --> 03:55.254
That's better!

03:56.797 --> 03:58.674
What the hell was that on stage?

03:58.674 --> 04:00.927
What you wanna go do another encore?

04:00.927 --> 04:03.095
No, I don't wanna do
another bloody encore!

04:03.095 --> 04:05.389
You were supposed to play my song!
You didn't!

04:05.389 --> 04:09.602
Yeah, well, I'm...I'm sorry.
I-I-I just forgot.

04:09.602 --> 04:11.270
You forgot?!
Yeah.

04:11.270 --> 04:14.815
Well, the next time you forget, I'm
gonna knock your head in the ground!

04:14.815 --> 04:17.485
OK, OK! Let's get
all these people out of here!

04:17.485 --> 04:19.695
Hey, Whittler,
get 'em all out of here!

04:19.695 --> 04:22.740
Come on! Everybody out.
Excuse me, ladies. Thank you.

04:22.740 --> 04:26.494
We're ready to go, Dwayney boy.
So much for tonight's entertainment!

04:26.494 --> 04:28.329
WHITTLER: Yes, you two. Out of here!

04:28.329 --> 04:29.830
Well, what about me?

04:29.830 --> 04:34.335
Oh, well, the more the merrier,
I always say! (GROWLS)

04:34.335 --> 04:35.503
(CHUCKLES)

04:35.503 --> 04:37.713
We need something to remind us.
Remember that.

04:39.298 --> 04:42.635
Hey, hey, Tonic. What are you doing?

04:42.635 --> 04:44.887
I'm just gonna take my make-up off.

04:44.887 --> 04:47.056
(LAUGHTER)

04:47.056 --> 04:49.308
How many times
do we have to go over this?

04:49.308 --> 04:51.894
The make-up adds an air of mystery,
and mystery means...

04:51.894 --> 04:53.646
BOTH: Record sales.

04:53.646 --> 04:55.815
You don't take off the make-up
until...

04:55.815 --> 04:58.984
ALL: We get back to the hotel!

04:58.984 --> 05:01.737
Before me, you guys were nothing.
And so were you!

05:01.737 --> 05:03.155
Huh, nothing?

05:03.155 --> 05:05.950
I came up with the idea for make-up
and now look!

05:05.950 --> 05:08.577
You guys are playing
in front of 90,000 fans.

05:08.577 --> 05:11.622
So let's not spoil a good thing, OK?
Come on. Give us a kiss!

05:11.622 --> 05:16.961
We're hear, and we obey!
Oh, come on! Let's go! Come on!

05:16.961 --> 05:19.422
(FANS SCREAMING)

05:22.383 --> 05:24.427
(INDISTINCT CHATTING)

05:25.636 --> 05:27.471
Guard it with your life.

05:27.471 --> 05:30.391
Hey, Tonic, what the hell
were you doing tonight on stage?

05:30.391 --> 05:31.976
You guys sounded horrible!

05:31.976 --> 05:34.437
Maybe it was the lyrics.
But you wrote them!

05:34.437 --> 05:37.898
Come on, lads. Get ready for this.
OK, let's, let's do it!

05:37.898 --> 05:40.151
Oh, God, I hate being a superstar!

05:40.151 --> 05:42.653
(SCREAMING)

06:03.799 --> 06:07.094
Bog off,
you bunch of bleeding piranhas!

06:12.850 --> 06:16.103
Maybe you wanna take it a little easy
with that stuff, huh?

06:16.103 --> 06:18.105
Just cos you can't hold
your own liquor,

06:18.105 --> 06:21.066
there's no reason to go sounding
like a bloody bumper sticker!

06:21.066 --> 06:23.944
You don't wanna pass out
and miss all the fun, huh?

06:23.944 --> 06:25.571
Ha! I AM the fun!

06:25.571 --> 06:27.531
(LAUGHS)

06:27.531 --> 06:29.283
Especially when he's snoring.

06:29.283 --> 06:33.829
I bet you've never fallen asleep
on a girl, have you?

06:33.829 --> 06:34.997
(CHUCKLES)

06:34.997 --> 06:38.751
Well, a gentleman w-would never...
would never kill.

06:38.751 --> 06:40.961
Unless he's alone with his mates!

06:40.961 --> 06:44.673
You can bet your pounds on that!

06:44.673 --> 06:49.220
Speaking of which, how much
are we making tonight, Dwayney boy?

06:49.220 --> 06:50.471
We did OK.
OK?

06:50.471 --> 06:52.806
We had 80,000 screaming fans
out there!

06:52.806 --> 06:56.268
And 80 tons of equipment
and 80 roadies and crew.

06:56.268 --> 06:58.854
Not to mention the hotels
and the limos.

06:58.854 --> 07:00.272
Or, or T-shirt sales.

07:00.272 --> 07:02.024
Or your personal living expenses

07:02.024 --> 07:04.318
which have to be paid for
by the corporation.

07:04.318 --> 07:06.695
Which is us, right? Right?

07:08.447 --> 07:10.741
Right, Tonic?
Yeah. Right.

07:10.741 --> 07:13.994
And I say the corporation
wants to buy me a Ferrari!

07:13.994 --> 07:17.748
Don't you think you'd be smarter
investing your money
instead of wasting it on toys?

07:17.748 --> 07:21.835
I don't wanna invest!
Flash McGrath wants to spend!

07:21.835 --> 07:25.005
That's like really smart(!)
What?

07:25.005 --> 07:28.342
I-I think what Dwayne
means to say is that, uh,

07:28.342 --> 07:30.719
we should all save our money
for a rainy day.

07:30.719 --> 07:35.265
Let it pour!
We have more money than Croesus!

07:35.265 --> 07:39.436
We're gonna make The Beatles
look like ants. Yeah? Aren't we?

07:39.436 --> 07:40.938
(CHUCKLES)

07:40.938 --> 07:42.731
I don't remember them.

07:43.774 --> 07:44.858
Huh?

07:44.858 --> 07:49.196
I-I mean, that's what people are
gonna be saying about The Beatles,

07:49.196 --> 07:52.116
"I don't remember them,"
you know, when we get really big!

07:52.116 --> 07:54.868
I mean, The Beatles,
they're like an insect infestation!

07:57.621 --> 08:00.165
Yeah!
And we're the bloody exterminators!

08:00.165 --> 08:02.209
(RAUCOUS LAUGHTER)

08:10.509 --> 08:12.636
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

08:12.636 --> 08:16.098
I'm coming, I'm coming! Hold
your horses! I'll be right there!

08:16.098 --> 08:18.475
Who is it?

08:18.475 --> 08:20.394
Surprise!

08:20.394 --> 08:21.395
(SCREAMING)

08:23.397 --> 08:25.232
No, listen!

08:25.232 --> 08:28.277
Do I...do I know you girls?

08:28.277 --> 08:30.988
All right. That's it now.
You better get out of here.

08:30.988 --> 08:32.948
How did you girls get past security?

08:32.948 --> 08:35.659
We used our feminine wiles,
if you know what I mean.

08:35.659 --> 08:38.662
Well...
And we'd like to use 'em on you too.

08:38.662 --> 08:41.664
Look, look, I'm very flattered, OK,
but right now I'm really-

08:41.664 --> 08:44.168
Tired?
Oh, I know how to wake you up.

08:44.168 --> 08:46.253
No...

08:46.253 --> 08:49.131
Well, I must say this is a neat way
to get undressed.

08:50.257 --> 08:53.927
No, no, no! Don't do that!
Leave those on! Leave...

08:55.387 --> 08:58.974
Girls, you're gonna have to...
You're gonna have to leave!

08:58.974 --> 09:01.185
Girls...
We don't wanna leave! Let us stay!

09:01.185 --> 09:03.061
(SCREAMING)

09:03.061 --> 09:05.397
Thanks for coming!
Sam, they just got here!

09:05.397 --> 09:08.108
I appreciate it!
Oh, no! Please don't make us leave!

09:08.108 --> 09:10.611
Please! We wanna stay!
No! Don't make us leave!

09:10.611 --> 09:13.447
Oh, goody!
No!

09:13.447 --> 09:15.949
(SCREAMS)

09:15.949 --> 09:18.035
No, no...
I only wanna talk!

09:18.035 --> 09:19.953
Sam, what are you doing?!

09:20.871 --> 09:24.124
You're throwing away
a perfectly good fan sandwich!

09:24.124 --> 09:26.293
(BANGING ON DOOR)

09:26.293 --> 09:31.173
Oh, Sam!
Sometimes you are just pitiful!

09:31.173 --> 09:35.928
Why? Because...I won't take advantage
of some deluded girls who are...

09:37.721 --> 09:40.474
..throwing themselves at me
like some bad writer's dream?

09:40.474 --> 09:41.892
Yes!

09:41.892 --> 09:44.311
Look, Al, this is demeaning to them!

09:45.437 --> 09:47.856
This is worse than when I was
a Chip 'N Dales dancer!

09:47.856 --> 09:51.318
Yeah, but they're dying
to be demeaned with you! Repeatedly.

09:52.861 --> 09:55.614
I swear, it boggles the mind!

09:55.614 --> 09:57.491
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

09:57.491 --> 10:01.411
Look, I'm gonna boggle you!
Now, tell me, what is going on?

10:01.411 --> 10:03.247
Not much.

10:03.247 --> 10:06.458
OK, OK, OK, OK!

10:06.458 --> 10:08.919
April 12th, 1974.

10:08.919 --> 10:11.630
Your name is Jeffrey Mole,

10:11.630 --> 10:14.591
and you're the lead singer
in an English rock group

10:14.591 --> 10:16.260
called King Thunder.

10:16.260 --> 10:19.429
Yeah. I never heard of them before.
You were a nerd back then.

10:19.429 --> 10:21.223
You wouldn't know them.

10:21.223 --> 10:24.935
Your nickname is Tonic,
which is short for Vodka Tonic,

10:24.935 --> 10:27.354
which relates
to some drinking escapade

10:27.354 --> 10:29.106
you had early in your career.

10:29.106 --> 10:31.775
So, what, I'm here to help them play
Madison Square Garden,

10:31.775 --> 10:33.860
or become bigger
than The Beatles, right?

10:33.860 --> 10:35.445
No, no. You don't remember?
What?

10:35.445 --> 10:37.781
This was big news.
It was in the papers, on TV.

10:37.781 --> 10:38.907
What?

10:38.907 --> 10:41.702
Well, two night from now,
right after the concert,

10:41.702 --> 10:46.915
some crazy nut stabs you just
as you're getting into your limo.

10:48.083 --> 10:49.251
You get killed.

11:01.035 --> 11:03.287
So who kills me? 
Who kills Tonic?

11:03.287 --> 11:05.414
We don't know.
He disappeared into the crowd.

11:07.041 --> 11:11.045
How can you stab somebody
in front of hundreds of witnesses,
and then just disappear?

11:11.045 --> 11:13.714
I'm trying to tell you
what happened. I can't explain it.

11:13.714 --> 11:18.594
It was probably some nutcase
like that Mark David Chapman.

11:18.594 --> 11:21.806
Who?
The rat that shot John Lennon.

11:23.849 --> 11:27.812
Al, I...I saw
somebody like that today.

11:27.812 --> 11:30.147
You did? What did he look like?

11:31.732 --> 11:37.697
Uh...blond. Uh, young. 16 or 17.

11:37.697 --> 11:41.701
He had on an army jacket and...
What?

11:43.369 --> 11:46.163
Well, a k-kind of
a...haunted expression.

11:46.163 --> 11:50.167
Well, Ziggy can't find anyone
that fits that profile
in your probability matrix.

11:50.167 --> 11:51.544
It must be a stranger.

11:51.544 --> 11:55.089
Why would a complete stranger wanna
kill me? That doesn't make sense!

11:55.089 --> 11:57.550
You're the one with all the PhDs.
You tell me!

11:57.550 --> 11:59.635
(SIRENS WAIL IN THE DISTANCE)

12:01.679 --> 12:05.391
Process schizophrenia.
Yeah, that's a possibility.

12:05.391 --> 12:08.686
Oh, yeah. Yeah, sure.
Process schizophonic, yeah.

12:08.686 --> 12:10.604
No, no. Process schizophrenia.

12:11.856 --> 12:13.899
Most schizophrenics
never become violent,

12:13.899 --> 12:17.486
but in process schizophrenia
a person's sense of self

12:17.486 --> 12:19.321
is slow in developing.

12:19.321 --> 12:22.992
It's kind of like they don't have
a complete personality,

12:22.992 --> 12:27.246
so they fill up what's missing
by imitating something that they see.

12:27.246 --> 12:29.498
Like that kid
who shot President Regan.

12:29.498 --> 12:31.167
Oh, Hinckley?
Yeah, Hinckley.

12:31.167 --> 12:33.711
He repeatedly watched
Taxi Driver, the movie,

12:33.711 --> 12:36.964
over and over again, about this guy
who stalks a political candidate.

12:36.964 --> 12:38.090
Yeah.
Yeah.

12:38.090 --> 12:40.509
And then the rest is history,
as they say.

12:40.509 --> 12:44.555
Yeah, right. But we don't even know
if that's what this guy is or...

12:44.555 --> 12:47.975
According to Ziggy, these anonymous
killers come in all types.

12:47.975 --> 12:51.896
Most of them are obsessive
and some of them are loners.

12:51.896 --> 12:55.441
If you ask them about their lives,
they say one thing but in reality-

12:55.441 --> 12:58.652
The truth is completely different.
That's right.

12:58.652 --> 13:01.864
And this one is apparently obsessed
with you, with Tonic.

13:01.864 --> 13:03.824
Yeah.

13:03.824 --> 13:06.994
Listen, on this leap,
I want you to stay really close, OK?

13:06.994 --> 13:09.914
Because if we see him, I don't wanna
take a chance on losing him.

13:09.914 --> 13:11.415
I'll stick with you like glue.

13:13.542 --> 13:14.543
Right.

13:28.015 --> 13:30.267
MAN: Rock and roll!

13:30.267 --> 13:34.104
WFGF! We got the beat
and we got the heat, man!

13:34.104 --> 13:37.024
Hey, you're back on the case
with Eliot Chase.

13:37.024 --> 13:39.735
Listen, we're broadcasting live
today from a rather-

13:39.735 --> 13:42.112
A rather tacky establishment.

13:42.112 --> 13:45.282
Yeah, t-thank you. Yes, it is
a rather tacky shopping mall here.

13:45.282 --> 13:47.952
If you're just turning in, man,
you have been missing out,

13:47.952 --> 13:51.121
because my very special guest
with me right now is King Thunder!

13:51.121 --> 13:53.207
(CHEERING)

13:54.708 --> 13:58.003
All right. Tonic, let me just talk
to you for one second here.

13:58.003 --> 14:01.048
Your last album, Five All Night,
was heavy, man.

14:01.048 --> 14:05.552
The best track on it by far
was Faith's Wide Wheel.

14:05.552 --> 14:08.430
How did you write that song?

14:08.430 --> 14:10.015
Holding a pen.

14:10.015 --> 14:11.267
(LAUGHTER)

14:11.267 --> 14:14.728
Yeah! Yeah, but I mean,
what was going through your mind?

14:14.728 --> 14:17.356
Well, nothing. He hasn't got one!
(LAUGHS)

14:17.356 --> 14:20.693
Honestly, Tonic's got a great mind.
Oh, yes.

14:20.693 --> 14:24.697
It's just a bit of bother to get him
to think about something besides...

14:24.697 --> 14:26.824
Besides women,
you were gonna say, right?

14:26.824 --> 14:29.326
Yeah, well, who can blame him?

14:29.326 --> 14:31.954
But if I can get back on track
for just one second.

14:31.954 --> 14:34.665
Tonic, what were you thinking
when you wrote,

14:34.665 --> 14:40.045
"As I travel in space and time,
I wanna stay, I wanna go.

14:40.045 --> 14:43.632
You can see my face,
but it's not mine.

14:44.800 --> 14:47.928
What you can't see,
you'll never know"?

14:47.928 --> 14:50.097
What can't we see?

14:50.097 --> 14:52.558
Our ugly faces for one thing.

14:52.558 --> 14:54.893
Why do you think we wear
this bloody make-up?

14:54.893 --> 14:56.478
(LAUGHS)

14:56.478 --> 15:03.110
Well, I guess what I,
what I really was...meaning to say

15:03.110 --> 15:11.869
was, uh, that...
we all live our lives behind masks.

15:13.203 --> 15:14.955
But the real point of living

15:14.955 --> 15:20.002
is to get beyond,
to break through those masks,

15:20.002 --> 15:24.673
from the outside and from the inside,
so that we can really communicate.

15:27.718 --> 15:30.637
Unfortunately, most of us don't.

15:30.637 --> 15:33.849
That's so true.
Great, great!

15:36.894 --> 15:39.438
Hi.
Hi.

15:44.818 --> 15:47.321
Do you have something for me to sign?
Uh, yeah.

15:49.948 --> 15:52.034
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

15:59.208 --> 16:00.209
Thanks!

16:00.918 --> 16:04.087
Do come back soon! All right!

16:05.380 --> 16:06.381
Al!

16:14.890 --> 16:16.016
Got him!

16:16.016 --> 16:17.643
Excuse me, Tonic?

16:17.643 --> 16:21.688
Oh...I, I thought I saw

16:21.688 --> 16:24.775
someone that I hadn't seen
in a really, really long time.

16:24.775 --> 16:27.861
But I-I guess it really wasn't him.

16:27.861 --> 16:32.616
Gushie, he's still moving.
Keep me centred on him.

16:32.616 --> 16:35.619
Tonight's gonna be your next-to-last
concert in Detroit, right?

16:35.619 --> 16:38.997
Right, and we'll be world-premiering
some new songs, which I've written.

16:38.997 --> 16:42.125
Really? What? Now that's a first.
You must be really excited.

16:42.125 --> 16:46.630
Oh, not at all, actually, cos I know
Tonic's gonna do a bang-up job!

16:46.630 --> 16:48.173
(CHUCKLES)

16:49.299 --> 16:51.927
It should really be exciting.
Looking forward to it!

16:51.927 --> 16:53.387
Yeah. (CLEARS THROAT)

16:58.600 --> 17:02.604
♪ I'm just a traveller
upon the scene

17:02.604 --> 17:06.942
♪ The time of life
of faith's wide wheel ♪

17:08.609 --> 17:13.448
All right, kid, what is your story?
What are you up to?

17:14.907 --> 17:19.621
Let me see. April 23rd, 1974.

17:20.747 --> 17:24.876
This is room 23, so according
to the records, your name...

17:24.876 --> 17:29.881
Your name is...John Doe.
Damn! That's a big help!

17:29.881 --> 17:30.966
(HUMS)

17:30.966 --> 17:32.592
Oh, I see.

17:32.592 --> 17:37.389
There must be something around here
with your name on it.

17:38.932 --> 17:40.142
Traveller!

17:40.142 --> 17:42.477
Can you give me a little hint,
a little clue here?

17:44.354 --> 17:47.357
Come on! What's your name?
Give me a break!

17:47.357 --> 17:50.152
I don't know!
How do these private eyes do it?

17:50.152 --> 17:52.237
(CONTINUES TO HUM)

17:59.453 --> 18:00.495
What was that?

18:04.583 --> 18:08.045
Thanks. Philip Silbart.

18:08.045 --> 18:15.802
Born July 27th, 1957.
Hastings, Nebraska.

18:15.802 --> 18:18.513
(CHUCKLES) Gotcha!

18:23.226 --> 18:26.897
SAM: 'Leaping about in time has put
me into some unusual situations,

18:26.897 --> 18:30.567
but some leaps are definitely
more difficult than others.

18:30.567 --> 18:32.944
It's one thing to study lyrics
and guitar charts

18:32.944 --> 18:34.821
in the privacy
of your own hotel room,

18:34.821 --> 18:37.199
but it's another thing
to remember them

18:37.199 --> 18:39.993
when you're in front
of 80,000 screaming fans.'

18:41.536 --> 18:43.955
Where have you been?
Huh?

18:43.955 --> 18:47.125
Oh, I've been, I've been running
some scenarios through Ziggy

18:47.125 --> 18:48.877
on this kid, Philip Silbart.

18:48.877 --> 18:50.712
You found out his name. What else?

18:50.712 --> 18:55.550
Of course I... Oh, well,
he was born in Hastings, Nebraska.

18:55.550 --> 18:59.429
He was raised by his mother,
Priscilla, and his...

18:59.429 --> 19:01.139
Oh, that poor kid's illegitimate.

19:01.139 --> 19:05.227
Anyway, his mother died in 1970,

19:05.227 --> 19:08.480
two years after they lost this
little farm they were living on.

19:08.480 --> 19:10.524
And since then
he's been running away

19:10.524 --> 19:13.318
from a series of foster homes
and county agencies.

19:13.318 --> 19:17.864
His social worker says
he's emotionally disturbed.

19:17.864 --> 19:21.117
Anyway, Ziggy thinks
he's gonna end up homeless,

19:21.117 --> 19:22.911
and he's a perfect candidate.

19:22.911 --> 19:24.246
Well, look-
Tonic?

19:24.246 --> 19:27.791
Some bank bloke called for you
from Utah about a ranch.

19:28.959 --> 19:30.919
Uh...a ranch?

19:30.919 --> 19:32.963
He wanted me to give you a message.

19:32.963 --> 19:37.384
He said your cheque bounced
and unless you give him another one,

19:37.384 --> 19:39.553
you can't do it.

19:39.553 --> 19:41.263
OK. Thanks.

19:42.138 --> 19:44.516
Any time!

19:44.516 --> 19:48.061
Let's get this sound check
over with. I'm starving!

19:48.061 --> 19:50.438
I-I gotta talk with Philip.

19:50.438 --> 19:53.984
Man, this kid doesn't want to talk
to you. He wants to kill you!

19:53.984 --> 19:57.028
Now, come on!
You gotta rehearse the song!

19:57.028 --> 20:00.407
Just rock the redhead.
And plug that in.

20:03.368 --> 20:04.828
One, two, three!

20:04.828 --> 20:06.580
(OUT OF TUNE)
# She stood six foot four

20:06.580 --> 20:07.872
♪ Barely fit through the door

20:08.498 --> 20:11.334
♪ But the hair was the colour of fire

20:11.334 --> 20:15.130
♪ She said, "Baby, what you need
is some horizontal speed

20:15.130 --> 20:17.632
♪ And I'm the one to take your desire

20:17.632 --> 20:21.553
♪ Baby, let me take you higher

20:23.930 --> 20:26.850
♪ Rock the redhead all night

20:26.850 --> 20:30.103
♪ Rock the redhead so right

20:30.103 --> 20:32.731
♪ Rock the redhead... ♪

20:34.232 --> 20:35.608
(GRUNTS)

20:35.608 --> 20:38.820
Whoa! Tonic, are you all right?
Are you OK, Sam?

20:38.820 --> 20:42.324
I think so.
I just banged my head a little.

20:42.324 --> 20:44.409
Oh, damn!

20:44.409 --> 20:47.912
It might have knocked
some sense into him!

20:47.912 --> 20:50.040
Where's Philip?
Philip?

20:51.207 --> 20:52.667
Maybe it did hit him after all.

20:52.667 --> 20:56.004
He's still back in his hotel room.
He couldn't have done this.

20:56.004 --> 20:59.799
Tonic, are you OK?
How the hell did this happen?

20:59.799 --> 21:03.428
Something must have come loose.
Oh, no kidding, Sherlock!

21:03.428 --> 21:06.556
Maybe it was just an accident.
Unless somebody else did it.

21:06.556 --> 21:08.808
A rest, a hot shower,
and you'll be as good as new.

21:08.808 --> 21:12.812
Whittler, I want you to find out
who's responsible for this!

21:12.812 --> 21:15.398
You got sloppy! And then get
this thing back up there.

21:15.398 --> 21:17.901
And this time make sure it stays!
Yeah, sure.

21:17.901 --> 21:21.738
Everyone back to the hotel!
We've got a big night ahead of us!

21:21.738 --> 21:23.239
Yeah, I'm coming.

21:23.239 --> 21:26.076
The only safe place for these drums
is off stage!

21:26.076 --> 21:28.203
Maybe Philip set this thing up
in advance.

21:28.203 --> 21:31.998
Well, even if he could have, how
could he have triggered that thing

21:31.998 --> 21:33.166
to make it fall?

21:33.166 --> 21:36.544
How do you know?
Especially since he's not even here.

21:36.544 --> 21:38.755
He couldn't.
Not unless he's a psychic.

21:38.755 --> 21:41.049
Like one of those guys
that can bend spoons.

21:42.133 --> 21:43.635
OK, so Philip didn't do it,

21:43.635 --> 21:45.929
so we're back to it
either being an accident,

21:45.929 --> 21:47.680
or somebody else setting it up.

21:47.680 --> 21:50.809
It had to be someone
who could get past security.

21:51.810 --> 21:56.606
Unless security did it.
Have anything on Whittler?

21:56.606 --> 22:00.068
Rode with a biker gang,
a bunch of arrests.

22:00.068 --> 22:02.487
Ah, did two years for armed robbery.

22:02.487 --> 22:06.950
And once he, he was arrested
for attempted manslaughter.

22:06.950 --> 22:08.660
But he wasn't convicted.

22:08.660 --> 22:10.787
He's real buddy-buddy with Flash.

22:10.787 --> 22:14.624
And Flash would become the leader
of this band if...

22:14.624 --> 22:17.377
If you went up to the big amplifier
in the sky.

22:27.849 --> 22:29.809
DEWAYNE: Who is it?
Tonic.

22:29.809 --> 22:32.145
Oh, come in, Tonic. 
The door's open.

22:35.106 --> 22:38.192
Tonic, what are you doing here?
You're supposed to be resting.

22:38.192 --> 22:40.361
Yeah, I know.
I-I just wanted to talk to you.

22:40.361 --> 22:42.572
You got a second?
Sure. What's on your mind?

22:44.157 --> 22:46.868
You know that ranch
I'm buying in Utah?

22:46.868 --> 22:48.703
Ranch? What ranch?

22:48.703 --> 22:53.833
My bank called today.
Told me that the cheque bounced.

22:53.833 --> 22:55.793
Of course the cheque bounced!

22:55.793 --> 22:58.880
I don't leave money lying around
in your check-in account.

22:58.880 --> 23:01.132
I've got it working for you.
I understand that-

23:01.132 --> 23:04.343
I've told you a million times not to
go off on these wild spending sprees

23:04.343 --> 23:06.095
without talking to me first.

23:06.095 --> 23:08.931
That way I can transfer the right
amount of money to your account.

23:10.099 --> 23:14.020
OK, OK. The damage is done.
Why don't you tell me how much money
you've blown this time?

23:14.020 --> 23:17.148
Uh, well, a lot. Sort of.

23:17.148 --> 23:20.985
And now it's a ranch, eh? What
do you want with a ranch, anyway?

23:22.320 --> 23:27.241
I just want a ranch. There's no
problem with the money, is there?

23:27.241 --> 23:31.621
No, no! It's just tied up
in long-term stuff.

23:31.621 --> 23:32.872
If we cash in right now,

23:32.872 --> 23:35.708
well, we won't make quite
as much money as we could have.

23:35.708 --> 23:39.462
Get me the name of the bank and I'll
get a cheque to them right away.

23:40.922 --> 23:44.717
Yeah, well, I-I got..
I got the number back in my room,

23:44.717 --> 23:46.969
so I-I'll just go
and I'll get it to you later, OK?

23:46.969 --> 23:49.305
Right. Then I'll call them.

23:49.305 --> 23:53.017
And you can go and play Roy Rogers
to your heart's content!

23:53.017 --> 23:56.229
Now go and get some rest, Tonic.
You got a big night, tonight.

24:01.025 --> 24:02.401
Right.

24:05.029 --> 24:08.950
'This is WFGF Radio here with you
King Thunder maniacs

24:08.950 --> 24:11.410
partying down at the arena!

24:12.870 --> 24:16.666
I want to give a special welcome
to all of you WFGF fans...'

24:16.666 --> 24:19.335
Are you hiding out, Sam?
Why do you always do that?!

24:19.335 --> 24:21.420
Sorry!
Now, look at me.

24:21.420 --> 24:24.131
I cannot do this! I am not a rocker!

24:24.131 --> 24:27.260
You can do this, Sam!
I can't do it!

24:27.260 --> 24:30.596
I'm gonna go out there and they're
gonna hear me sing, and kill me!

24:30.596 --> 24:32.598
I mean,
I don't sing like those people!

24:32.598 --> 24:35.643
When I grew up,
I listened to Simon & Garfunkel.

24:35.643 --> 24:38.062
Sam, they're not gonna kill you.
They're not!

24:38.062 --> 24:41.315
All you do is you go out there and
you make an idiot out of yourself.

24:41.315 --> 24:43.234
Oh, fine.
Yes! They'll eat it up!

24:43.234 --> 24:45.528
That's what they expect
of rock stars!

24:45.528 --> 24:47.822
I don't have the faintest idea
of how to act.

24:47.822 --> 24:50.574
These people, they got a whole style.

24:50.574 --> 24:52.159
Do Hendrix!

24:52.159 --> 24:55.913
You take to the guitar like this
and you go... (MAKES GUITAR NOISE)

24:55.913 --> 24:58.332
He used to pick the guitar
with his teeth.

24:58.332 --> 24:59.458
Hendrix?
Yeah.

24:59.458 --> 25:02.336
Or do Townshend.
Who?

25:02.336 --> 25:04.255
That's right.
What is?

25:04.255 --> 25:06.674
Who.
I don't know.

25:06.674 --> 25:08.884
Townshend!
Who?

25:08.884 --> 25:11.595
Yeah, that's right.
Pete Townshend of The Who.

25:11.595 --> 25:12.930
Of the what?!
Never mind.

25:12.930 --> 25:16.767
He used to do the windmill.
Like that, you know.

25:16.767 --> 25:20.771
If it really gets desperate
and they start charging up on stage,

25:20.771 --> 25:22.898
and they're gonna rip
your clothes off,

25:22.898 --> 25:26.277
you stick your tongue out as far as
you can and you wiggle it like that.

25:26.277 --> 25:29.530
That is gonna make them stop
from ripping my clothes off?

25:29.530 --> 25:32.074
No, that'll make them start
ripping their clothes off.

25:32.074 --> 25:34.660
Then you can take the guitar
and you can smash it to pieces.

25:34.660 --> 25:36.078
That always gets 'em!

25:36.078 --> 25:38.456
Al, with my luck,
they're gonna want an encore,

25:38.456 --> 25:39.999
and I'm not gonna have a guitar-

25:39.999 --> 25:42.835
Don't worry, Sam!
Just go out there and cut loose!

25:42.835 --> 25:44.879
I'm gonna be with you
the whole time.

25:44.879 --> 25:49.175
If worse comes to worse,
do Milli Vanilli.

25:49.175 --> 25:51.844
Who?
That's what I suggested first!

25:51.844 --> 25:54.013
RADIO ANNOUNCER: King Thunder!

25:54.013 --> 25:55.389
Come on!

