(CHEERING)

27:57.928 --> 28:00.264
We love you, Detroit!

28:02.516 --> 28:04.560
(ROCK MUSIC IN THE BACKGROUND)

28:08.147 --> 28:10.190
Nice party.
Yeah.

28:11.650 --> 28:14.695
Hey, hey, hey! What's going on?

28:14.695 --> 28:17.489
We thought you could use
a bit of cheering up, Tonic!

28:17.489 --> 28:20.242
Well, what I could really use
is a little quiet.

28:20.242 --> 28:21.869
Ah, all right. No problem.

28:23.662 --> 28:25.080
(SHOUTS) Quiet!

28:28.459 --> 28:31.003
Hey, no problem, man.

28:33.797 --> 28:35.758
Oh, hi. How are you doing?

28:35.758 --> 28:38.677
Listen,
I-I-I'll talk to you later, OK?

28:38.677 --> 28:41.221
Hey, hey! Hey, come here!

28:43.057 --> 28:44.808
(CHUCKLES)

28:44.808 --> 28:48.937
How about a nice little
vodka tonic, Tonic?!

28:48.937 --> 28:50.314
(LAUGHS)

28:50.314 --> 28:51.648
Thanks, I'll pass!

28:51.648 --> 28:54.568
That's good!

28:54.568 --> 28:57.362
You should be in costume!

28:57.362 --> 28:59.615
He's right, mate!

28:59.615 --> 29:02.159
Listen... I'm sorry! Excuse me.

29:02.159 --> 29:04.244
Excuse me... Oh, hi, Sandy. Sorry.

29:04.244 --> 29:06.038
You wanna do it again?

29:06.038 --> 29:08.832
Uh, well, no. Not really, not really.

29:08.832 --> 29:12.169
Oh, Tonic...I've got this...

29:15.631 --> 29:16.715
..problem.

29:16.715 --> 29:18.092
Take a look!

29:18.092 --> 29:20.969
(CHUCKLES) Your bird, right?

29:20.969 --> 29:22.846
Come on, come on!

29:22.846 --> 29:25.390
Well, I-I'm sure
that Flash can handle it.

29:25.390 --> 29:31.772
Well, Flash can handle just about
anything except...a real woman.

29:31.772 --> 29:35.818
Yeah, well...that's, that's great.
I'm glad you told me that.

29:35.818 --> 29:40.572
I really don't think it's wise to go
swimming in another man's pool.

29:40.572 --> 29:43.909
I'm not in another man's pool.
Especially if that man is Flash.

29:43.909 --> 29:48.080
Uh, l-look, S-Sandy... (CHUCKLES)

29:48.080 --> 29:52.084
Uh, I-I'm sure whatever the thing is,
the problem is he can handle it.

29:52.084 --> 29:55.170
If you just give him a chance...
Oh, but I wanna give YOU the chance.

29:55.170 --> 29:58.715
Oh, thanks, thanks. But why don't
we talk about this tomorrow, OK?

29:58.715 --> 30:00.175
Or next week?

30:00.175 --> 30:03.887
(GIGGLES)
I wanna do more than just talk.

30:05.430 --> 30:07.015
Ciao.

30:07.015 --> 30:09.351
Ciao.
Ciao.

30:16.316 --> 30:20.821
Al, it's five o'clock in the morning.
Don't these people ever go home?

30:22.864 --> 30:26.660
Tonic, what, you lost in space?
It's your party, mate!

30:26.660 --> 30:28.078
Yeah, you're right!

30:28.078 --> 30:32.541
Ziggy says there's a 60% chance
that Dwayne is embezzling you guys.

30:32.541 --> 30:35.210
That's how come your cheque bounced.

30:35.210 --> 30:38.630
The trail is kind of fuzzy,
but it appears

30:38.630 --> 30:41.633
that he's been trading and losing
more money on the stock market

30:41.633 --> 30:43.218
than he makes in a year.

30:43.218 --> 30:47.097
What about Whittler?
17% chance to knock you off.

30:47.097 --> 30:49.391
Al, there's gotta be a prime suspect,

30:49.391 --> 30:52.185
so just have Ziggy
go over the scenarios again.

30:52.185 --> 30:55.314
Well, it looks like
a three-way toss-up.

30:55.314 --> 30:59.026
Everybody seems to be
equally looking guilty or innocent,

30:59.026 --> 31:00.944
depending on which way
you look at it.

31:00.944 --> 31:04.906
Yeah, well, then, we're gonna have
to keep a close eye on everybody.

31:04.906 --> 31:06.366
Yeah.

31:08.702 --> 31:10.412
Where's Philip right now?

31:10.412 --> 31:15.292
I don't know.
Gushie, centre me on Philip.

31:18.378 --> 31:21.965
Gushie, quit fooling around!
I'm trying to find Philip!

31:21.965 --> 31:23.967
He says he's here.
What?

31:23.967 --> 31:27.262
Also, he says there's a fifty-fifty
chance that you get it now.

31:27.262 --> 31:28.847
Now?
Yeah, at the party.

31:52.079 --> 31:54.456
Whittler!
Hey, you're hurting my arm!

31:54.456 --> 31:56.416
What's wrong?
How did this kid get in here?

31:56.416 --> 31:59.044
He must have slipped by
when Eddie was on the door.

31:59.044 --> 32:00.754
These kids are all alike.

32:00.754 --> 32:03.090
They get in here
and steal everything they can.

32:03.090 --> 32:05.801
I didn't steal anything!
What do you call this?

32:05.801 --> 32:08.845
Sam, that's part of your costume.
What else you got on you?

32:11.098 --> 32:13.266
What about this knife?

32:13.266 --> 32:14.476
Take it easy, would you?

32:14.476 --> 32:17.437
Look, I don't wanna hurt you,
but I don't wanna get hurt either.

32:17.437 --> 32:18.980
I'd never hurt you.

32:20.440 --> 32:23.985
You're my father.
You're his father?

32:23.985 --> 32:29.032
Ah, next time, be sure
to check your raincoat, sport!

32:29.032 --> 32:32.202
Come on.
No, w-w-wait a second.

32:32.202 --> 32:35.664
Listen, I-I'm gonna talk to this...
What's your name?

32:35.664 --> 32:40.252
Philip. Philip Silbart.
Philip here. It's cool. Come on.

32:48.593 --> 32:50.220
(SIGHS)

32:52.138 --> 32:54.057
So what makes you think
that I'm your father?

32:55.809 --> 33:00.438
Mu mom told me. She always had
your picture around and...

33:00.438 --> 33:02.148
And your albums.

33:05.277 --> 33:09.281
And one day she started crying
and...and she told me.

33:09.281 --> 33:11.992
Told you that I was your father.
She said that...

33:12.951 --> 33:16.037
You know, you...you did it
after your concert in Omaha,

33:16.037 --> 33:18.415
the first time you guys
came over here from England.

33:18.415 --> 33:22.961
Well, Sam, King Thunder
did play Omaha 16 years ago.

33:22.961 --> 33:25.589
Of course then they were called
The Dingles.

33:26.798 --> 33:28.884
Things do happen after concerts.

33:28.884 --> 33:33.305
Look, Philip, I was in Omaha a
long time ago, but that doesn't mean-

33:33.305 --> 33:34.973
I sound like you.
What?

33:34.973 --> 33:36.975
I can play guitar just like you.

33:38.810 --> 33:41.438
I sing just like you.
That's because you're my father.

33:41.438 --> 33:43.857
A lot of people
have very similar voices

33:43.857 --> 33:45.734
and sound alike when they sing.

33:46.943 --> 33:49.279
Look.
You and I have got the same hand.

33:49.279 --> 33:53.241
See, I got this little web of skin
just like you.

34:06.046 --> 34:08.757
I don't want any money from you.

34:08.757 --> 34:13.011
I don't want anything. I just want
you to admit that you're my father.

34:22.130 --> 34:24.675
SAM: 'Even though Philip and I
share the set of webbed fingers,

34:25.887 --> 34:29.306
there was still only a 50% chance
I was his father,

34:29.306 --> 34:31.726
but a 99% chance
I was still going to get killed.

34:31.726 --> 34:33.395
That meant to catch the killer,

34:33.395 --> 34:36.313
I was still going to have
to do the concert.'

34:36.313 --> 34:38.733
(CHUCKLES) What the hell is that?

34:38.733 --> 34:40.819
Ah, someone nicked me bloody wig!

34:40.819 --> 34:43.321
I'll have the roadies
go out and fetch another one.

34:43.321 --> 34:45.364
Stupid fans!

34:45.364 --> 34:49.536
Just remember,
tonight we do my songs, right?

34:51.121 --> 34:52.414
Right.

34:52.414 --> 34:53.581
(CHUCKLES)

34:53.581 --> 34:57.877
Right. Then let's get this
bleeding thing over with, all right?

34:57.877 --> 35:00.547
Right!
Right! Bloody right!

35:00.547 --> 35:02.716
Hey, Kev, where are we?

35:02.716 --> 35:04.551
Uh, Detroit.

35:04.551 --> 35:07.053
BOTH: Hello, Detroit!

35:07.053 --> 35:08.096
AL: Sam!

35:09.222 --> 35:11.516
Hey, Whittler,
will you take this up for me?

35:11.516 --> 35:13.435
Yeah.
I'll be right out.

35:17.313 --> 35:22.110
I just...I just...think that you...
I think you should bail out of this.

35:22.110 --> 35:24.112
I can't bail out of this, Al!

35:24.112 --> 35:27.365
I gotta...I gotta figure out
who kills Tonic and stop him!

35:27.365 --> 35:28.491
No, well, I-

35:28.491 --> 35:31.035
Hey, Tonic, what are you doing?
We're ready for you.

35:31.035 --> 35:34.247
Oh, yeah. Well...
Yeah, I'm coming right out. Coming!

35:34.247 --> 35:37.709
Hey, Dwayne, uh...gotta talk to you
for a second, man.

35:42.338 --> 35:45.467
Listen, how much money of ours
have you lost

35:45.467 --> 35:48.011
on the stock market so far this year?

35:48.011 --> 35:51.264
None! I mean,
stocks go up and down, but...

35:51.264 --> 35:55.518
Dwayne, I had a friend check in
to your private account.

35:55.518 --> 35:57.604
Now, you've been gambling
more than you make.

35:57.604 --> 35:59.564
That money's coming from somewhere.

35:59.564 --> 36:01.441
And I'd hate to call
for a personal audit,

36:01.441 --> 36:04.152
because I think we both know
where that money's coming from.

36:04.152 --> 36:06.654
Tonic, it just got
a little bit away from me.

36:06.654 --> 36:10.366
Ah, see? I told you!
He's the killer! You slimy weasel!

36:10.366 --> 36:14.704
I can get it back. Give me time.
You can have all your money now.

36:14.704 --> 36:16.873
But you've just got
to give me the chance.

36:24.214 --> 36:27.091
OK. OK.

36:27.091 --> 36:29.385
Thanks, man.

36:29.385 --> 36:33.348
And, Dwayne...tonight when we leave,
after the concert,

36:33.348 --> 36:35.975
I don't wanna ride
in the same limo with Flash.

36:35.975 --> 36:41.105
And...and bring all the limos around
to a different exit, you know,

36:41.105 --> 36:43.107
because I-I-I hate that exit!

36:43.107 --> 36:45.568
OK. Whatever you say.
OK? I'm sick of it.

36:45.568 --> 36:48.571
OK. And...thanks, man.
OK.

36:50.865 --> 36:52.408
(EXHALES)

36:52.408 --> 36:55.495
You know, that idea
about the limos is great.

36:55.495 --> 36:57.372
I always say play it safe.

36:57.372 --> 36:59.040
Tonic?
Huh?

36:59.040 --> 37:01.751
Don't be coy with me, Tonic.

37:04.462 --> 37:10.218
I can see it in your eyes.
You were just pretending last night.

37:10.218 --> 37:14.222
You want me, and I want you.

37:14.222 --> 37:16.891
What about me?
Oh, boy!

37:16.891 --> 37:18.184
You got it.

37:18.184 --> 37:22.313
What?! Dwayne told me you were here!

37:22.313 --> 37:23.815
Get out! Go on!

37:23.815 --> 37:25.775
Look...Flash...

37:28.403 --> 37:30.238
You are a dead man!

37:32.907 --> 37:35.451
I told you! It's Flash!
He's the killer!

37:35.451 --> 37:38.329
And he doesn't wanna kill you
about his songs.

